2) Infinite Graphs(infinite number of edges or vertices)
3) Trivial Graph(Single vertex with no edge)
4) Simple Graph (does not have more then one edges between vertices)
5) Multi Graph(parallel edges and no loop)
7) Complete Graph (if each vertex have edges (n- 1) connected with other vertex)
8) Pseudo Graph (self loop and have multiple edges)
9) Regular Graph(All vertex have same number of edges)
